cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.GR, cs.CG, cs.AI 

This paper deals with learning geometric elements in images or 3D objects, which is a common problem in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also presents optimization algorithms for solving the associated problems, which falls under computational geometry (cs.CG) and optimization (cs.GR). Additionally, the use of proximal operators suggests a connection to convex optimization and regularization, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
